# health-front continuity guardrails

- Extend existing structure; do not re-architect working flows unless explicitly requested.
- Favor shared primitives in `@/components/ui/*` (Button, Card, Input, ModalShell, ConfirmModal, table and base controls) before creating page-specific variants.
- Keep styling token-first via `app/globals.css` variables (`--surface*`, `--text-*`, `--brand-*`, semantic tokens). Avoid hardcoded black/white or one-off hex colors in feature code.
- Preserve API contracts and RBAC behavior when making UI changes (no payload/status/permission logic drift).
- Keep pages lean and server-first: data/auth in `app/**/page.tsx`, interactive state in colocated client components.
- For dense dashboard screens, prioritize information hierarchy and compact spacing over decorative wrappers.
- Reuse established patterns:
  - CRUD toolbar + table shells for manager pages.
  - ModalShell for form/content dialogs and ConfirmModal for short confirmations.
  - Conditional rendering of optional sections (for example, guardian-related blocks only when relevant data exists).
